<TITLE> Global trade talks face big risk of failure: EU </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MASERU, Lesotho, Feb 29 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A six-year push for a global trade deal faces a high risk of failure, EU Trade Commissioner Peter Mandelson said on Friday. "Let me say emphatically on Europe's behalf, we will work all hours to achieve a fair and balanced outcome," Mandelson said in a speech to trade ministers from some of the world's poorest countries meeting in Lesotho. "But I now fear that Doha is facing a high risk of failure -- the first failure ever for a multilateral trade round." The World Trade Organisation is expected to call a meeting of top trade officials in March or April to press for a breakthrough in its Doha round of negotiations, which risks running out of time ahead of the US presidential electio
